title.narrative: Output 2.1.1: By December 2015, government commitment to scale up high-impact nutrition interventions is enhanced based on evidence demonstrated in at least three districts in three provinces.
Guidelines on micronutrient supplementation for children 6-23 months and pregnant women developed

baseline.value: 1999 guidelines reflect outdated iron-folate formulation for pregnant women, no guidelines on use of micronutrient powders for children age 6-23 months

actual.value: 2015:Updated guidelines on micronutrient powders for children aged 6-23 months (2012) and Ministerial Decree on MNP formulation (2012) developed. title.narrative: National legislation on the international code of marketing of breastmilk substitutes is adopted and monitoring and enforcement mechanism is identified.

target.value: 2015:Legislation is passed, institutionalized with monitoring and enforcement mechanism identified.

actual.value: 2015:Government Regulation Number 33/2012 on Exclusive Breastfeeding has been passed. Together with existing legislation that prohibits the marketing of Breastmilk Substitutes for children aged less than one year, the legislation in Indonesia now covers "many" of the provisions of the International Code

title.narrative: Policy framework and implementation guidelines for the Scaling Up Nutrition (SUN) Movement in Indonesia developed

baseline.value: No policy framework or implementation guidelines for the SUN Movement

target.value: 2015:Policy framework and implementation guidelines for the SUN Movement developed

actual.value: 2015:Policy Framework and Implementation Guidelines on the First 1000 Days of Life Movement developed.
